{
  "stem": "3964.6",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I couldn't swim, so obviously I stayed on the barge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Daylight broke about 8 o'clock, maybe early, 7o'clock.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "The SS came back with the tug boat and realized and also saw that quite a few people swimming on land.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "They went back on land, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] rounded up whoever was on land, marched them into the water, and killed them all, shot them all.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Must have been about 40 or 50 people who had made it on land.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Meantime, we're still on the-- on the barge.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The noise of the cannon fire is getting closer.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Airplanes are appearing overhead with British insignias on it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And now the SS in a tug boat disappears completely.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're nowhere to be seen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we are sitting on this barge, not knowing, should anyone else try to get onto land or not?",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "About 9 o'clock, aside from the cannon fire, we're hearing tremendous of-- amount of noise.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Couldn't figure out what it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Didn't know.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "No idea.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we knew that the end was near.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Approximately 9:30, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we saw British tanks rolling along the road approximately 500 feet from where we were anchored in the water.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And there was no SS.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were free to make noise and identify ourselves.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Seemingly, some of the people who had escaped earlier had gotten away and were intercepted, or had intercepted these tanks, told the British tank crew that there was a ship out there with us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they stopped in line with where we were anchored.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "There were several small boats laying on land.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Manned the boats, rowed to the boat, to the-- to the barge where we were in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And of course, they identified themselves and said they were British soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
